<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Configure Amazon EFS</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 1 minute to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><b>Note:</b> The Operations Bridge suite supports both EFS and NFS file systems. Skip this section and see <a href="./itom/Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ConfigureNFSServer" title="Operations Bridge:2019.05/ConfigureNFSServer">Configure NFS</a> if you plan to use NFS.
</p>
<ol><li>Create a new Security Group to control access to the EFS.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsB201905 ConfigureAFS1.png" src="/mediawiki/images/e/ee/OpsB201905_ConfigureAFS1.png" width="680" height="330" data-file-width="680" data-file-height="330"></a></li>
<li>Create the file system from the AWS EFS console.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsB201905 ConfigureEFS2.png" src="/mediawiki/images/b/b3/OpsB201905_ConfigureEFS2.png" width="348" height="126" data-file-width="348" data-file-height="126"></a></li>
<li>Select the VPC and select the private subnets from all Availability Zones.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsB201905 ConfigureEFS3.png" src="/mediawiki/images/b/b7/OpsB201905_ConfigureEFS3.png" width="694" height="341" data-file-width="694" data-file-height="341"></a></li>
<li>Add a Name tag (optional) and select General Purpose for the performance mode.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsB201905 ConfigureEFS4.png" src="/mediawiki/images/8/82/OpsB201905_ConfigureEFS4.png" width="703" height="300" data-file-width="703" data-file-height="300"></a></li>
<li>Review the settings and create the file system. Once the file system it is created review the details and note the DNS name associated with the EFS.</li></ol>

